      </div>

      <p>The scientific rationale for elderberry immune support centers on its effect on cytokine signaling. Anthocyanins from <em>Sambucus nigra</em> have been shown <em>in vitro</em> to increase production of inflammatory cytokines including IL-1 beta, IL-6, IL-8, and TNF-alpha — proteins that coordinate the immune response to viral and bacterial pathogens. A 2004 study published in the <em>Journal of International Medical Research</em> found that elderberry extract (Sambucol) reduced flu symptoms by an average of 4 days compared to placebo in patients with confirmed influenza B infection.</p>

