      <h2>How We Tested These Elderberry Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>Every recommendation in this guide is based on independent product evaluation, ingredient verification, and cross-referencing with published clinical research. Here is our complete testing process:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Independent Purchase:</strong> All 8 products were purchased at full retail price from authorized retailers including Amazon, Walmart, Target, CVS, and brand direct websites. We accepted no free samples, sponsorships, or affiliate incentive payments that could influence our rankings. Editorial independence is non-negotiable.</li>
          <li><strong>Elderberry Content Verification:</strong> We confirmed each product's elderberry source (Sambucus nigra vs. other species), extract concentration, standardization claims, and third-party testing certifications by cross-referencing supplement facts panels with manufacturer Certificates of Analysis (COAs) where available.</li>
          <li><strong>Clinical Literature Review:</strong> Each product's formulation was compared against the published clinical trial database on PubMed. We evaluated whether the elderberry type, dose, and complementary ingredients matched those used in studies demonstrating statistically significant immune outcomes.</li>
          <li><strong>Six-Week Testing Panel:</strong> A panel of 12 adults (ages 25-60) tested each product for a minimum of four weeks, with our top four picks extended to six weeks spanning cold season. Participants reported perceived immune health, energy levels, and any side effects using standardized daily logs.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste and Compliance Assessment:</strong> Each product was scored on flavor, texture, aftertaste, and ease of daily use on a 1-10 scale. Compliance determines real-world effectiveness — a great-tasting gummy taken consistently outperforms a potent product that gets forgotten in the cabinet.</li>
          <li><strong>Value Analysis:</strong> We calculated true cost per serving, assessed the quality and quantity of complementary ingredients (vitamin C, zinc, D3, echinacea), and determined whether each product's price-to-quality ratio was justified relative to competitors at the same tier.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Products were scored on a weighted scale: Elderberry Quality and Dose (30%), Third-Party Testing (20%), Complementary Ingredients (20%), Taste and Compliance (15%), and Value (15%). The rankings reflect these composite scores.</p>
