        <p>Elderberry is most effective when taken consistently, particularly during cold and flu season (October through March). Unlike fast-acting cold medications, elderberry works by supporting your immune system's readiness to respond — not by suppressing symptoms after you are already sick. Start supplementation in early fall, take your chosen gummy daily, and maintain the habit through the end of winter for maximum preventive benefit. The clinical evidence for elderberry's immune-supporting properties is strongest for consistent, daily use over weeks to months.</p>
